page Object Repository technique / POM techniques

https://www.selenium.dev/documentation/test_practices/encouraged/page_object_models/

page object modal or page factory is a java designed pattern preferred by 
google to implement object repository.

Rule #1 - As per the POM create a dedicated java file for each available screen in 
application and store page specific webElements (locators) in that particular file. 
eg. Login.java

Rule #2 - As per the POM, object identification can be done by 2 ways - 
@FindBy & @FindBys

Rule #3 - In order to create the objects of java classes available in page object 
repository we should take the help of PageFactory class.

